I have been to various events at the Fort Hamilton Community Club and this review is only for the lounge/bar. The lounge area has usually been open Thursday through Sunday. Several weeks ago I stopped by on a Sunday looking forward to watching football. The gentleman working there informed me that the lounge was not open and would not be going forward on Sundays. Ok... The following week, I stopped by to watch Thursday night football and was informed that only one satellite dish/box was working. Ok... I was regulated to watching hockey on all of their tv’s until the gentleman who was there watching hockey decided to leave (almost halftime of the football game). I stopped by tonight (two weeks later!) again hoping to watch Thursday night football. However, there is still only one operational dish/box and there were a couple people already watching the baseball game.  I understand that this is a small base on an Army/military scale, but that’s no excuse for what I’ve witnessed the past several weeks. I have been in the Army for 20 years and this is the worst community club/lounge/club situation I’ve experienced. I’m glad that this base is open to the community. However, if the bottom line is profit (weddings, parties, pool, etc) and catering to civilians and not MWR for soldiers, then it should be renamed the Bay Ridge Community Club. Only gave two stars because the bartenders were always attentive and professional.
